# Reference only — Dockhold never reads a committed .env. Set variables in the
# dashboard; put secrets (API keys, tokens) in the Vault. Server code reads
# them from process.env at runtime — route handlers, server components.
#
# Browser-visible values need the NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix and are baked into the
# build. The build doesn't see dashboard variables, so set these in code (e.g.
# next.config.js) — and only ever for PUBLIC values, never a secret.
#
# PORT is provided by Dockhold at runtime — the start script reads it.
# Enable the managed database add-on and Dockhold injects DATABASE_URL.
